                <fr:title text="Biinverse">Biinverse</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>biinverse</fr:strong></fr:em> to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a pair of a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>. We will refer to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> equipped with a biinverse as a <fr:em><fr:strong>biinvertible function</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>19</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>3194</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-000X</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-000X.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-inverse</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>quasi-inverse</fr:strong></fr:em> to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f \colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g \colon  B \to  A]]></fr:tex> equipped with homotopies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \colon  f \circ  g \sim  1_{B}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  g \circ  f \sim 1_{A}]]></fr:tex>, rendering <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> simultaneously a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                <fr:p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ]]></fr:tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <fr:em>unit</fr:em> and <fr:em>counit</fr:em> of the quasi-inverse.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>19</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>3195</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-000W</fr:addr>
