</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is called an <fr:em><fr:strong>embedding</fr:strong></fr:em> when for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the action on identifications <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  x=y\to  fx=fy]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">invertible</fr:link>.</fr:p>
