            <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-0047.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Being an embedding is a proposition">Being an <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">embedding</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0047.agda" type="external">erct-0047.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>That a given function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">embedding</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>5397</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">//erct/unstable/492</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-erct-unstable-492.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001B.xml" title="Dependent product of propositions" addr="//erct/erct-001B" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001B" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0044.xml" title="Being invertible is a proposition" addr="//erct/erct-0044" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-0044" /></fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>18</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>20265</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-0048</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-0048.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Embeddings are propositional"><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">Embeddings</fr:link> are <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0048.agda" type="external">erct-0048.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Any <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">embedding</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>3442</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">//erct/unstable/493</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-erct-unstable-493.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We must check that for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="//erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>. Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_0,u_1:\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,b]]></fr:tex> we must check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_0=u_1]]></fr:tex>. We let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a_0,p_0\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\equiv  u_0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen a_1,p_1\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\equiv  u_1]]></fr:tex> so that we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_0\colon  fa_0=b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_1\colon  fa_1=b]]></fr:tex>. Invoking the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0010.xml" title="Path object" addr="//erct/erct-0010" type="local">path object</fr:link> structure on <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="//erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fibers</fr:link> (<fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001R.xml" title="Path object structure on fibers" addr="//erct/erct-001R" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001R" /></fr:link>), it suffices to exhibit the following data:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   \phi &\colon  a_0 = a_1\\
   \psi &\colon  p_0 = \mathsf {act}_{f}\phi \cdot  p_1
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>As <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001K.xml" title="Contractible types are propositions" addr="//erct/erct-001K" type="local">embedding</fr:link>, the map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  a_0 = a_1 \to  fa_0 = fa_1]]></fr:tex> has an <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen \mathsf {act}_{f}^{-1},\epsilon ,\eta ,\chi \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha  \colon  fa_0 = fa_1]]></fr:tex> be the concatenation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_0\cdot  p_1^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. Therefore we may define:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   \phi &\colon  a_0 = a_1\\
   \phi &:\equiv  \mathsf {act}_{f}^{-1} \alpha 
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>To define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi  \colon  p_0=\mathsf {act}_{f}\phi \cdot  p_1]]></fr:tex> we use the counit of our <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> as we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  \alpha  \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\phi  = p_0\cdot  p_1^{-1}]]></fr:tex>. Thus concatenating on either side with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_1]]></fr:tex> we have our goal, modulo the laws of identification concatenation and symmetry respectively.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>18</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>20266</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-0049</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-0049.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Propositional maps are embeddings"><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">Propositional maps</fr:link> are <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">embeddings</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0049.agda" type="external">erct-0049.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Any <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional map</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">embedding</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>3444</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">//erct/unstable/494</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-erct-unstable-494.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> we must show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  x = y \to  fx=fy]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">invertible</fr:link>. By <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002C.xml" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses" addr="//erct/erct-002C" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-002C" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002D.xml" title="From biinverses to quasi-inverses" addr="//erct/erct-002D" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-002D" /></fr:link>, it suffices to exhibit a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000U.xml" title="Biinverse" addr="//erct/erct-000U" type="local">biinverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}]]></fr:tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> need not be identical).</fr:p>

 <fr:p>We first define the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}\colon  fx = fy \to  x = y]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is assumed to be <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link>, we have by <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001R.xml" title="Path object structure on fibers" addr="//erct/erct-001R" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001R" /></fr:link> an assignment <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi _{x,y}: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y,h^{-1}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. We therefore define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}h :\equiv  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \phi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
.1]]></fr:tex>; the witness of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sectionhood</fr:link> can be constructed using <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \phi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
.2]]></fr:tex> modulo some identification algebra.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>To construct the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000Y.xml" title="Section-retraction pair" addr="//erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retractions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}\colon  fx=fy\to  x = y]]></fr:tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,y}:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 =_{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y,h^{-1}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>, and we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}h :\equiv  \mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. It remains to show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon  x =y]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
=h]]></fr:tex>. By induction on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h]]></fr:tex> it suffices to show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex>. We will deduce that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl} = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex> from our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link> and thus <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">fibred in sets</fr:link> via <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001L.xml" title="Propositions are sets" addr="//erct/erct-001L" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001L" /></fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
