            <fr:title text="Full and faithful functor">Full and faithful <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000I.xml" title="Functor between precategories" addr="//erct/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000K.agda" type="external">erct-000K.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000I.xml" title="Functor between precategories" addr="//erct/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F\colon  C \to  D]]></fr:tex> is called (<fr:em><fr:strong>full</fr:strong></fr:em>, <fr:em><fr:strong>faithful</fr:strong></fr:em>) when the action on arrows is valued in (<fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0029.xml" title="Surjection" addr="//erct/erct-0029" type="local">surjections</fr:link>, <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003K.xml" title="Embedding" addr="//erct/erct-003K" type="local">embeddings</fr:link>) respectively. It is common to refer to a <fr:em>full</fr:em> and <fr:em>faithful</fr:em> functor as <fr:em><fr:strong>fully faithful</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Fullness and faithfulness are both <fr:em><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">properties</fr:link></fr:em> of a functor.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
